- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on studying bursting behavior on social media, specifically Twitter. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is also a likely category as the paper may involve software development for data collection and analysis. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is another possible category as the paper discusses the implications of the findings for predicting responses to information on social media. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) could also be a relevant category as the paper discusses the concept of Twitter as an excitable medium. 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper may involve natural language processing techniques for analyzing the keywords on Twitter.
